20 April 2021 The Government Communication and Information System in partnership with the Charlotte Mannya-Maxeke Institute will host a panel discussion as part of Freedom Month to commemorate the life and times of Charlotte Maxeke as a freedom fighter. Members of the media are invited to attend the panel discussion. Details are as follows: Date:  Wednesday, 21 April 2021Time: 11h00 to 12h00Platform:  Zoom: ID: 965 7484 5057Password: 414238 Panellists Media Participation: Journalists may view the webinar via steaming on the following social media links below: Facebook:    http://facebook.com/GovernmentZA Twitter:         http://twitter.com/GCISMedia http://twitter.com/GovernmentZA YouTube:     https://www.youtube.com/user/GovernmentZA RSVP: Cindy Ngozo on Email: CindyN@gcis.gov.za Enquiries: William Baloyi Cell: 083 390 7147